post_text: Our final senior highlight is Patrick O'Connor. Patrick is the son of Angela Edick. He has one brother, Chris Ferrare. After graduation Patrick plans to work at the Nodaway County Sheriff's Office and pursue an Associates Degree in Criminal Justice through NCMC. Patrick says morning basketball is what he will remember most about his time at Jefferson. He says back to back state basketball experiences is the school accomplishment he will remember most. Patrick's quote to live by is "When writing the story of your life, don't let anyone else hold the pen." -Drake

post_text: Dalton Luke is our senior highlight today. Dalton is the son of Mark and Veronica Luke. He has two brothers, Carter Luke and Andy Chor. After graduation Dalton plans to attend MidAmerica Nazarene University to major in pre-veterinary while getting the opportunity to continue his football career. Dalton says the lifelong friendships he has made as well as going to state basketball two years in a row are the things he will remember most about Jefferson. He said his school accomplishment he will most remember is being the first student from Jefferson to go on to play college football. Dalton’s quote to live by is "Turn the pain into power." -Arnold Schwarzenegger

post_text: Today we highlight Zachary Stoll. Zachary is the son of Steve Stoll and Vickie & Dean Crawford. After graduation he plans to attend NWMSU to major in public accounting with the goal of becoming a certified public accountant (CPA). When asked what he will remember most about his time at Jefferson, Zachary said, “All of the great personal connections I have made with staff, faculty, and students alike. I will especially remember working underneath John cleaning the school during the summer and school year.” The school accomplishment he will most remember is winning Grand Champion at the Missouri State Fair for FFA. Zachary’s quote to live by is "A five letter word for happiness...money." -Mr. Krabs

post_text:
We want to highlight our seniors as they wrap up their high school careers in an unprecedented way. Today we begin with Ashley Mattson.

Ashley is the daughter of Gary and Stacey Mattson. She has 2 sisters, Emily and Aubrey, and 1 brother, Andy. After graduation Ashley plans to attend nursing school at Missouri Western State University. When asked what she will remember most about Jefferson, Ashley said the love, support, and competitive nature of the Jefferson Family, as well as working in the summer with John and the rest of the summer custodial crew. She said the school accomplishments she will most remember are going to state her freshman year in softball and her senior year in basketball. Ashley's quote to live by is "Do not take life for granted, because you never know what tomorrow will bring."
